detector.name: Failure Anomalies
detector.description:
Detects if your application experiences an abnormal rise in the rate of HTTP requests or dependency calls that are reported as failed. The anomaly detection uses machine learning algorithms and occurs in near real time, therefore there's no need to define a frequency for this signal.

To help you triage and diagnose the problem, an analysis of the characteristics of the failures and related telemetry is provided with the detection. This feature works for any app, hosted in the cloud or on your own servers, that generates request or dependency telemetry - for example, if you have a worker role that calls

>A note about your data privacy:

The service is entirely automatic and only you can see these notifications.

>Read more about data privacy

Smart Alerts conditions can't be edited or added for now.

inputs.name: Query
inputs.value:
AzureActivity
| summarize uniqueCallersActive = dcount(Caller) by bin_at(TimeGenerated, 1h, now())
| render timechart

inputs.name: Query
inputs.value:
| summarize Current_Week = countif(TimeGenerated >= ago(7d)), Previous_Week = countif(TimeGenerated < ago(7d)) by Caller
| where Current_Week > Previous_Week
| extend growth = iif(Previous_Week != 0, toreal(Current_Week)/toreal(Previous_Week), toreal(Current_Week))
| sort by growth desc nulls last
| project Caller, Previous_Week, Current_Week , increased = strcat(\

inputs.value: //Get operation with most warning level logs\nAzureActivity\n| where Level == \
\n| summarize Count = count() by OperationName\n| top 10 by Count

inputs.name: Query
inputs.value: \n| summarize count() by bin_at(TimeGenerated, 1h, now()), ActivitySubstatus\n| extend ActivitySubstatus = iff(ActivitySubstatus == \

inputs.name: Query
inputs.value: //Time chart of Failed operations Code : 404 by hour\nAzureActivity\n| where ActivityStatus == \

| summarize 404_Errors = count() by bin_at(TimeGenerated, 1h, now())
| render timechart

inputs.name: Query
inputs.value: //number of logs over time scale of a week\nAzureActivity\n| summarize numOfLogs = count() by bin_at(TimeGenerated, 1h, now())

It was designed by the Internet Engineering Task Force (IETF) as an extension of the Secure Shell protocol (SSH) version 2.0 to provide secure file transfer capabilities.

detector.name: Failure Anomalies
detector.description:
Detects if your application experiences an abnormal rise in the rate of HTTP requests or dependency calls that are reported as failed. The anomaly detection uses machine learning algorithms and occurs in near real time, therefore there's no need to define a frequency for this signal.

To help you triage and diagnose the problem, an analysis of the characteristics of the failures and related telemetry is provided with the detection. This feature works for any app, hosted in the cloud or on your own servers, that generates request or dependency telemetry - for example, if you have a worker role that calls

>A note about your data privacy:

The service is entirely automatic and only you can see these notifications.
